<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="443" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/52.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-21"><hi rend="italic">June 21,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Cables under date of 11th and 18th received. Government of Liberia
                            officially informed the appointment of Falkner. Instructions <pb facs="0425" n="343" xml:id="pg_343"/> to American bankers cabled
                            to-day. Commission by mail as advised in cable. Full information by
                            cable after a meeting of the Cabinet.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lyon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>